f:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Sunsama is best suited for individuals, executives, mindful workers, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Todoist, meanwhile, shines for individuals, freelancers, GTD practitioners, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2016, Sunsama describes itself as \"Calm daily planner that pulls tasks from all your tools into one focused view.\" Todoist, established in 2007, positions itself as \"Simple and powerful task manager with natural language input and smart scheduling.\" With 9 years between them, Todoist brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Sunsama offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
10:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Todoist** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), more features (8 vs 6), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Sunsama is a poor choice — far from it. Sunsama excels in its own right, particularly for individuals and executives.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best natural language task input, go with Todoist. If beautiful daily planning ritual matters more to you, Sunsama is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
